FBIS4-29504 "dreas118_n_94012" FBIS-EAS-94-118 Daily Report 17 Jun 1994 Vietnam IMF Grants Vietnam $50-Million Loan IMF Grants Vietnam $50-Million Loan BK1906125094 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam in English 1000 GMT 17 Jun 94 BK1906125094 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam English BFN [Text] The International Monetary Fund has announced to grant Vietnam a loan of $50 million for the rehabilitation of economic development in Vietnam in 1994. Meanwhile the World Bank lent Vietnam credit for the upgrading of the section from Ho Chi Minh city to Can Tho and the section between Hanoi and Nhatrang on Highway No.1. The World Bank also provided loans for the improvement of primary education system and agricultural development program, including three such projects for agricultural credit, rubber plantation, and intensive farming. The World Bank expert said that in the coming three or four years, international credits to vietnam will reach $315 million per year.
